						<p>
				The term Decentralized finance (Defi) was coined by Ethereum co-founder, Vitalik Buterin in January 2018. The official Ethereum blog defines Defi as "applications (DApps) and organizations (DeCos) that run on blockchains with strong programmable transaction functionality like Ethereum".			</p>

						<p>
				A Complete Guide. DeFi, short for Decentralized Finance, is a term used to describe financial products that are built on permissionless and decentralized blockchains like Ethereum. This includes all sorts of exciting financial applications that offer lending, borrowing, trading, insurance and much more. The possibilities are almost limitless.			</p>

						<p>
				DeFi is the abbreviation for Decentralized Finance, which implies an assortment of financial applications that leverage blockchain networks and technologies. Decentralized Finance DeFi has introduced a formidable change in viewing financial transactions beyond the existing assumptions of the prevailing, closed financial market.			</p>

				
            
